1
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:14,633
I'm not sure if I can be away
from Mookie.

2
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:15,467
I don't want to.

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:17,067
Please let Emma return
to her job.

4
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:20,867
Don't give me another reason
to get mad at you again.

5
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:22,133
How is she doing?

6
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,833
I'm no longer working here.

7
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,200
Her mom fired me.

8
00:00:25,267 --> 00:00:27,800
I'm begging you.
Please forgive Emma.

9
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:29,233
Fine, fine! I will!

10
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:30,900
Think whatever you want.

11
00:00:30,967 --> 00:00:33,933
Will you believe me if I say
I want you to be happy?

12
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,467
I wonder what she looks like
when she was a kid.

13
00:00:37,567 --> 00:00:39,900
Didn't you see any pictures
of her in their house?

14
00:00:39,967 --> 00:00:41,033
I wonder why she doesn't
have any pictures.

15
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:42,767
I'm warning you, Emma.

16
00:00:42,833 --> 00:00:46,467
If you do it again,
I will not just fire you.

17
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:50,200
I will find a way to kick you
out of your house

18
00:00:50,267 --> 00:00:51,400
and out of this place.

19
00:00:51,467 --> 00:00:56,467
I want to know if Emma
will do what she promised.

20
00:02:19,467 --> 00:02:20,967
Put it there.

21
00:02:21,033 --> 00:02:23,867
Flor, I'm not allowed
to be here, right?

22
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:24,867
Yeah.

23
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:27,933
But Ma'am Olive isn't here.

24
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,067
So it's okay.

25
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:31,900
I heard she'll stay late
in the office today

26
00:02:31,967 --> 00:02:34,133
because Ma'am Astrid
is still in Cebu.

27
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,100
But Ma'am Astrid
will be back soon.

28
00:02:36,167 --> 00:02:37,833
- Is that so?
- Yes.

29
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:42,033
She can't blame me.

30
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:45,300
I need to do a lot of things.
I'm swamped with work.

31
00:02:45,367 --> 00:02:48,633
And she doesn't hire
additional helpers.

32
00:02:48,733 --> 00:02:50,167
Of course.

33
00:02:50,233 --> 00:02:53,167
Tell me whenever you need help.

34
00:02:53,233 --> 00:02:54,833
- Thank you.
- Yes.

35
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:59,467
But promise me you won't come
near Mookie again.

36
00:02:59,533 --> 00:03:01,700
- Please.
- Yes, yes. I won't.

37
00:03:01,767 --> 00:03:05,067
I'm glad you didn't come
near her yesterday.

38
00:03:05,133 --> 00:03:07,033
Oh my gosh, I was nervous.

39
00:03:07,100 --> 00:03:11,333
If you did,
we'd both get in trouble.

40
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,300
It's because of you.

41
00:03:15,100 --> 00:03:16,933
It's so dusty in here.

42
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:49,267
Hey.

43
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,700
Why do you seem so quiet?

44
00:03:52,767 --> 00:03:54,467
No, I just picked up
the sweeper.

45
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:56,400
Okay. Sweep that area.

46
00:03:56,467 --> 00:04:00,700
Ma'am Olive is sensitive
to dust.

47
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:03,667
Over there.

48
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:06,033
There, thank you again.

49
00:04:13,067 --> 00:04:14,433
Mommy Emma?

50
00:04:19,100 --> 00:04:20,167
Mookie?

51
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,467
Mookie.

52
00:04:23,733 --> 00:04:25,433
Why did you come here?

53
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,533
We can't talk.

54
00:04:43,767 --> 00:04:46,700
Mookie, I miss you so much.

55
00:04:46,767 --> 00:04:49,967
I wanted to hug you yesterday,
but...

56
00:04:50,033 --> 00:04:54,300
I didn't want to give your mom
a reason to fire me.

57
00:04:54,367 --> 00:04:57,367
I understand, Mommy Emma.

58
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:01,233
I miss you so much, too.

59
00:05:03,167 --> 00:05:07,433
But I guess you're right.

60
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,533
We better not see
each other for now.

61
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:14,267
Because I don't want us
to be away from each other.

62
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:18,067
How are you?

63
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:19,967
Are you okay?

64
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:21,700
Did your mom hurt you?

65
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:28,367
She also destroyed
the storybook.

66
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:30,633
It's okay, it can be replaced.

67
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:33,867
You're my only concern.
I'm worried about you.

68
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:37,067
I also don't think
I'll get better.

69
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:43,633
That's not true.

70
00:05:43,700 --> 00:05:44,733
You'll get better.

71
00:05:50,133 --> 00:05:51,100
Look.

72
00:06:03,033 --> 00:06:04,767
That's you.

73
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:15,100
Is this me, Mommy Emma?

74
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:16,833
Yes, Mookie. It's you.

75
00:06:16,900 --> 00:06:21,633
I saw it in your mom's office
when Flor and I cleaned it.

76
00:06:23,133 --> 00:06:26,200
Look. You were so healthy.

77
00:06:26,267 --> 00:06:28,267
You didn't seem ill.

78
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:37,133
But mommy told me that I had
been ill since I was a child.

79
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:40,300
Since she gave birth to me.

80
00:06:40,367 --> 00:06:42,267
I don't believe it, Mookie.

81
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,900
That picture is so clear.

82
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:46,933
You don't look sickly.

83
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,633
I believe you'll recover and
return to how you used to be.

84
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:51,833
Don't worry.

85
00:06:51,900 --> 00:06:54,767
I'll find a way to help you.

86
00:06:57,033 --> 00:06:58,600
Why, Mookie?

87
00:06:58,667 --> 00:07:00,333
Don't you believe me?

88
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:04,333
No, Mommy Emma.

89
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:12,600
She always tells me that
I will never get better.

90
00:07:12,667 --> 00:07:17,900
And I should be thankful
that I reached this age.

91
00:07:19,967 --> 00:07:23,067
You're the only person

92
00:07:23,133 --> 00:07:27,200
who told me that I still have
a chance to recover.

93
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:32,100
You know what?

94
00:07:32,167 --> 00:07:38,500
When I gave birth to my baby,
she was also weak. But I prayed.

95
00:07:38,567 --> 00:07:41,667
I believed and trusted God.

96
00:07:41,733 --> 00:07:43,400
Did she recover?

97
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:44,433
Yes.

98
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,200
She recovered.

99
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:50,200
God gave us a chance
to be together.

100
00:07:50,267 --> 00:07:54,367
If only a tragedy
hadn't happened,

101
00:07:54,433 --> 00:07:58,767
we still would've been together.

102
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:02,300
Don't cry.

103
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:06,833
Don't worry.

104
00:08:06,900 --> 00:08:09,667
I'll convince myself
that I will get better.

105
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:17,900
And this picture that you
gave me, I will keep this.

106
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:25,167
This will remind me that
someone wants me to recover.

107
00:08:25,267 --> 00:08:28,000
And that's you, Mommy Emma.

108
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:55,333
There you go, Emma.

109
00:08:55,433 --> 00:09:00,267
We changed your ringing tone
with your favorite song.

110
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:02,033
Thank you, Wiro.

111
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:05,233
Kutsy, thank you also for
letting me borrow your laptop.

112
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:06,333
You're welcome.

113
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:10,700
What will you search for?

114
00:09:10,767 --> 00:09:15,767
I want to research
about Ma'am Olive.

115
00:09:15,833 --> 00:09:21,433
But I want to know more
about Mookie's illness.

116
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:25,133
So that I can somehow help her.

117
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:28,033
What is the kid's illness?

118
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:33,667
I heard she has leukemia
and an autoimmune disease.

119
00:09:33,733 --> 00:09:37,067
She said she also has a problem
with her spinal cord.

120
00:09:37,133 --> 00:09:39,833
And she also has a panic attack.

121
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,667
I'm glad she's still alive.

122
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:43,567
Hey!

123
00:09:43,633 --> 00:09:45,567
Poor kid.

124
00:09:45,633 --> 00:09:48,667
She seems so sick.

125
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:51,400
I know.

126
00:09:51,467 --> 00:09:53,233
Are you still
approaching Mookie?

127
00:09:55,467 --> 00:09:57,000
Come on, Emma.

128
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:58,333
Yeah.

129
00:09:58,400 --> 00:10:01,000
And you act as if
you're her mother.

130
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,000
I agree.

131
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:09,833
Ma'am Olive seems
to neglect her.

132
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:12,733
I don't understand mothers

133
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:16,333
who neglect or give their
children up for adoption.

134
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:23,667
How can they bear
to see their kid suffer?

135
00:10:23,733 --> 00:10:25,467
You know what, Mom?

136
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:28,700
If Baby Kayla is alive,

137
00:10:28,767 --> 00:10:33,000
I won't let her get hurt
or be away from her.

138
00:10:44,933 --> 00:10:46,033
Mommy...

139
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:53,133
thank you for letting me
go out again.

140
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:55,533
Flor has to clean your room.

141
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:57,667
But, Flor, look after Mookie
for now.

142
00:10:57,733 --> 00:10:58,833
- Yes, Ma'am.
- I will just have to fix

143
00:10:58,900 --> 00:11:00,500
a machine, then you can start
cleaning after that.

144
00:11:00,567 --> 00:11:01,467
Okay, Ma'am.

145
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,433
Flor, can you make me
a smoothie?

146
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,767
Sure.

147
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,500
Stay here, okay?
I'll be right back.

148
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:36,533
Yes, Grace? Why did you call?

149
00:11:37,500 --> 00:11:39,833
Ma'am, I can't contact
Ma'am Olive.

150
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:42,800
That's why I called you.

151
00:11:42,900 --> 00:11:45,300
What is it about?
I'll just relay it to her.

152
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:48,400
We have delivered
Canixidol to her.

153
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:49,467
She made another order,

154
00:11:49,533 --> 00:11:51,867
but the next delivery
will take a while.

155
00:11:51,933 --> 00:11:54,533
Olive made another order
of Canixidol?

156
00:12:31,433 --> 00:12:32,433
Dammit!

157
00:12:33,733 --> 00:12:35,567
Mookie!

158
00:12:41,567 --> 00:12:42,533
Mookie!

159
00:12:43,567 --> 00:12:44,800
Mookie.

160
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:48,267
Why, Mommy?

161
00:12:54,533 --> 00:12:58,067
Why are you keeping this photo
in your room?

162
00:13:01,267 --> 00:13:04,333
Mookie, I'm asking you.

163
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,700
Did someone give this to you?

164
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:32,067
I don't understand mothers

165
00:13:32,133 --> 00:13:35,933
who neglect or give
their children up for adoption.

166
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:40,100
How can they bear to see
their children suffer?

167
00:13:40,167 --> 00:13:44,200
If Baby Kayla is alive,
I will never let her get hurt

168
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:46,700
or be away from her.

169
00:13:53,167 --> 00:13:54,167
Virgie?

170
00:13:55,367 --> 00:13:56,367
Virgie!

171
00:13:56,433 --> 00:13:57,833
Hey, Virgie!

172
00:13:57,900 --> 00:13:59,033
Virgie!

173
00:14:00,167 --> 00:14:01,667
Stop! Stop!

174
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:03,833
- Follow that tricycle!
- Okay.

175
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:08,100
Hurry!

176
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:18,867
Where did you get this photo?

177
00:14:20,767 --> 00:14:24,700
I'm asking you, so answer!

178
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:28,400
Why do you have this picture?

179
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:34,867
Your legs are useless,
but your mouth is working.

180
00:14:34,933 --> 00:14:37,267
So answer me!

181
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:39,700
Why do you have this?

182
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:46,100
No one gave it to me, Mommy.

183
00:14:46,167 --> 00:14:48,400
Then why is it in your room?

184
00:14:48,467 --> 00:14:50,233
Answer me!

185
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:53,100
How did you get this picture
if no one gave it to you?

186
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,767
Answer me!

187
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:58,733
I took that photo, Mommy.

188
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:01,067
You took it?

189
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:04,600
Tell her it came from me. Do it!

190
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:07,367
How did you get this?

191
00:15:07,433 --> 00:15:10,067
How did you get this picture?

192
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,100
I got it when I came
to your office

193
00:15:20,167 --> 00:15:25,800
and helped you pick up
your files, Mommy.

194
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:28,233
You little thief!

195
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:32,800
Who told you to get
this picture?

196
00:15:32,867 --> 00:15:35,233
Who told you to keep it?

197
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:39,167
Who told you? Answer me!
Say something!

198
00:15:39,233 --> 00:15:41,300
Why are you stealing from me?

199
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:43,500
Why did you steal this picture?

200
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:45,600
Why are you angry, Mommy?

201
00:15:45,667 --> 00:15:48,167
It's just a picture.

202
00:15:48,233 --> 00:15:51,967
Because you shouldn't
keep this picture!

203
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:56,967
Is it because I look healthy
in that picture, Mommy?

204
00:15:57,033 --> 00:16:01,167
- Is it because I'm not sick?
- Shut up!

205
00:16:01,233 --> 00:16:03,667
Why did you lie to me, Mommy?

206
00:16:03,733 --> 00:16:09,167
You told me I'd been sick
since I was a baby.

207
00:16:09,267 --> 00:16:10,933
This is just a picture.

208
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,933
You don't know your condition
at that time!

209
00:16:26,067 --> 00:16:29,400
It stopped. I'll get off.
Pull over. Stop.

210
00:16:34,867 --> 00:16:36,067
Here. Virgie! Virgie!

211
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:37,500
You can have all this, Mister.
Go!

212
00:16:37,567 --> 00:16:38,567
Virgie!

213
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:44,700
Ligaya? What are you doing here?

214
00:16:44,767 --> 00:16:46,733
We now live here.

215
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,767
How are you?

216
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:50,467
Have you found them?
Any updates?

217
00:16:50,533 --> 00:16:51,667
Yes, Ligaya.

218
00:16:51,733 --> 00:16:54,367
But I don't know
where to find you.

219
00:16:54,433 --> 00:16:56,733
I don't have your number.

220
00:16:56,800 --> 00:17:00,800
I heard that Ma'am Alice
is now back in the country.

221
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:03,000
Ever since I lost them,

222
00:17:03,067 --> 00:17:05,600
it seems like something in me
has been missing.

223
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:07,067
My being a mother.

224
00:17:07,133 --> 00:17:08,900
I don't feel whole.

225
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:12,967
There are a lot of things
I want to tell them.

226
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,833
I did them wrong.

227
00:17:15,933 --> 00:17:21,067
I'm sure they'll get hurt
when they see me.

228
00:17:22,300 --> 00:17:25,667
But I hope they can forgive me.

229
00:17:25,733 --> 00:17:32,900
I can't do anything
at that time.

230
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:38,767
All I know is that I did
what was best for them.

231
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:40,167
Thief!

232
00:17:40,233 --> 00:17:41,833
You're such a thief!

233
00:17:41,900 --> 00:17:43,267
You're ungrateful!

234
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:47,567
How could you steal from me
after everything I did for you?

235
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:49,533
Don't you believe me?

236
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:51,233
You're sick!

237
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,733
Just accept that you're sick,

238
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:54,433
and that you will never
get better!

239
00:17:58,133 --> 00:17:59,267
Flor!

240
00:17:59,333 --> 00:18:00,933
What are you doing, Emma?

241
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,267
Come here. What do you think
you're doing?

242
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:05,600
Ma'am Olive is hurting Mookie.

243
00:18:05,667 --> 00:18:08,867
Leave it be.
We can't do anything.

244
00:18:08,933 --> 00:18:10,733
Doesn't she feel bad
for the kid?

245
00:18:10,800 --> 00:18:12,533
Does she always do this?

246
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:15,767
I don't know if she does that
when they're in the room.

247
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:19,233
This is the first time I've seen
her hurting Mookie like that.

248
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:23,033
Stop, please.

249
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:24,633
Flor! Hurry up!

250
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:27,033
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Help me get Mookie upstairs.

251
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:28,367
- Yes, Ma'am. I'm coming.
- I will put her

252
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:31,000
- in the dark room. Hurry up!
- Yes, Ma'am.

253
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,567
Thief.

254
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:43,567
What's their address?

255
00:18:43,633 --> 00:18:45,833
Where do they live?
Please give it to me.

256
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,267
I don't know.

257
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:49,633
The person who told me
doesn't know, too.

258
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:53,667
Son of a gun, Virgie.

259
00:18:53,733 --> 00:18:55,633
What's wrong with you?

260
00:18:55,733 --> 00:18:58,967
I was perspiring while trying
to catch you.

261
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,900
And I even paid for my commute,
and now, you're telling me

262
00:19:02,967 --> 00:19:06,333
you don't know Ma'am Alice's
address?

263
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:09,133
Don't you know where they live?

264
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,700
Son of a bread, Virgie.

265
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:14,733
Give me your new number.

266
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:18,100
I will contact you once I get
Ma'am Alice's address.

267
00:19:20,333 --> 00:19:21,833
I'll wait for it.

268
00:19:24,600 --> 00:19:26,300
There.

269
00:19:26,367 --> 00:19:28,633
Go ahead, Flor. Go upstairs.

270
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:30,967
Okay, Ma'am.

271
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:33,200
I'll take care of Mookie.

272
00:19:33,267 --> 00:19:34,500
Okay, Ma'am.

273
00:19:39,867 --> 00:19:43,300
Mommy, why are you hurting me?

274
00:19:46,600 --> 00:19:50,067
Because you did something wrong.

275
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:54,433
Is it because of my old photo?

276
00:19:56,167 --> 00:19:59,200
I was so happy when I saw it.

277
00:20:00,900 --> 00:20:04,733
But why don't you seem happy,
Mommy?

278
00:20:04,833 --> 00:20:08,700
Why do you always seem
to want me to be sick?

279
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:11,567
Because you really are sick.

280
00:20:11,633 --> 00:20:13,933
And I can't do anything
about it.

281
00:20:16,467 --> 00:20:18,200
I don't believe it, Mookie.

282
00:20:18,267 --> 00:20:20,667
The picture is so clear.

283
00:20:20,733 --> 00:20:22,800
You don't look sickly.

284
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:27,433
I believe that you'll go back
to how you used to be.

285
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:28,467
Maybe...

286
00:20:30,100 --> 00:20:33,033
it's because you don't love me.

287
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,000
You don't love me, Mommy.

288
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,700
You don't love me.

289
00:20:36,767 --> 00:20:39,800
You don't love me.

290
00:20:39,867 --> 00:20:41,700
You don't love me.

291
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:43,333
How dare you say that?

292
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:49,767
You don't know what sacrifices
I made just for you!

293
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:55,100
Because Mommy, you won't hurt me
if you love me!

294
00:20:55,167 --> 00:20:58,767
You'll want me to get better
if you love me!

295
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:02,033
You'll want me to recover,
Mommy!

296
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,333
Won't you stop?

297
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:09,333
You're talking back to me.

298
00:21:09,433 --> 00:21:12,300
And you stole something
from me.

299
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:15,600
Your horns must be cut off!

300
00:21:30,133 --> 00:21:31,567
Where's Mookie?

301
00:21:46,133 --> 00:21:50,233
What I needed to sacrifice
for you!

302
00:21:50,300 --> 00:21:53,233
You'll want me to get better
if you love me, Mommy!

303
00:21:53,300 --> 00:21:54,867
You won't stop?

304
00:21:58,467 --> 00:22:00,500
You're talking back to me now?

305
00:22:03,033 --> 00:22:04,967
Mommy.

306
00:22:05,033 --> 00:22:06,567
Mommy, no.

307
00:22:06,633 --> 00:22:09,167
I don't want it here, Mommy.

308
00:22:09,233 --> 00:22:11,233
Mommy, I don't want to be here.

309
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:13,500
- You don't want it here?
- Please.

310
00:22:13,567 --> 00:22:17,467
You should've thought about that

311
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:23,700
before you stole
and talked back to me.

312
00:22:23,767 --> 00:22:25,400
Please help me.

313
00:22:25,467 --> 00:22:27,700
How can I help Mookie?

314
00:22:27,767 --> 00:22:29,400
You keep on talking back to me?

315
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,600
Mommy.

316
00:22:40,300 --> 00:22:42,867
You're not going anywhere...

317
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:45,567
until I say so.

318
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:50,033
Mommy!

319
00:22:50,133 --> 00:22:52,733
Don't! Mommy, I won't be able
to breathe!

320
00:22:52,800 --> 00:22:54,933
- Mommy, please! Mommy!
- You deserve that.

321
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:58,500
- Mommy, no.
- You don't need these medicines

322
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:01,433
because you said so.

323
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,700
Mommy!

324
00:23:10,633 --> 00:23:13,167
Why did you order
a lot of Canixidol?

325
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:15,333
Is this for Mookie again?

326
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,533
Mommy Emma?

327
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:20,533
Don't dare meddle with my plans.

328
00:23:21,967 --> 00:23:23,700
- Give it to me!
- Let go of that!

329
00:23:23,767 --> 00:23:24,700
Astrid!

330
00:23:24,767 --> 00:23:26,800
Emma's not coming home.

331
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:28,033
Mother...

332
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:29,967
Just leave her be.

333
00:23:30,033 --> 00:23:31,800
- What are you saying?
- That's what makes her happy.

334
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:34,333
You're my source of strength.

335
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,967
I'll be brave for you.

336
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:41,233
Mother's calling.
